b'' b'' b'what you can do if you want three-prong outlets without additional wiring is' b'to use a gfci outlet (or breaker, but the outlet will be cheaper). in fact,' b'depending on where you are putting your new outlet(s), a gfci may be *required*.' b'' b'you still need to supply a proper ground for a ground fault circuit interrupter!' b'' b"oddly enough, you don't, at least according to the wiring faq that" b'is regularly posted on misc.consumers.house.' b'' b'a gfci senses discrepancies between the live and neutral wire currents,' b'and cuts them both off if a discrepancy is found. no ground connection' b'is needed for it to function.' b'' b'' b'' b'--' b':- michael a. covington, associate research scientist b':- the university of georgia phone b':- athens, georgia u.s.a. amateur radio n4tmi 